The White House announced100 pct tariffs on 300 mln dlrs worth of Japanese electronicgoods, effective Friday.    The tariffs were imposed because of alleged Japanesefailure to honor an agreement to stop below cost dumping ofcomputer microchips on world markets and to open up itsdomestic markets to American goods.    "I regret that these actions were necessary," PresidentReagan said in a statement.    Reagan said the tariffs would be eliminated "as soon as wehave firm and continuing evidence that the dumping in thirdcountry markets has stopped and that access to the Japanesemarket has improved."    He said he was encouraged by recent actions by Tokyo toimprove compliance with the U.S.-Japanese semiconductoragreement and he looked forward to the day when it was workingas effectively as it should. REUTER&#3;